<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="591" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1579,2018]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1856,1879]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
One pair of comma-shaped eyespots well separated from each other; nuchal scute and nuchal gland both absent; protrusion of the skin from VII a1 to VIII a2; papillae, sensillae and lines on the dorsal surface all absent; gonopores separated by one primary annulus; mid-body somites triannulated, ([a1]+[a2]+[a3]); one pair of salivary glands, compact; six pairs of gastric caeca, last pair forming post-caeca; ascendant portion of the ejaculatory ducts from XIII/XIV to XI/XII; six pairs of testisacs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="592" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[349,485,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Body shape.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[496,589,152,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="2.0">2–7 mm</quantity>
in length; maximum width ± 
<quantity box="[925,995,152,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
; body sublanceolate (
<figureCitation box="[1240,1304,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. External morphology of Helobdella buzz. A. Entire leech, dorsal view showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow); B. Entire leech, ventral view; C. Ventral view of the anterior end; D. Dorsal view of the anterior end showing the eyespots (arrows); E. Ventral view of the genital region showing male (M) and female (F) gonopores; F. Lateral view of the anterior end showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801143/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A and 1B), dorsoventrally flattened; anterior sucker well-developed, somewhat triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1029,1094,186,209]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. External morphology of Helobdella buzz. A. Entire leech, dorsal view showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow); B. Entire leech, ventral view; C. Ventral view of the anterior end; D. Dorsal view of the anterior end showing the eyespots (arrows); E. Ventral view of the genital region showing male (M) and female (F) gonopores; F. Lateral view of the anterior end showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801143/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
C); margin of annuli rounded, raised from body wall; head region somewhat triangular; posterior sucker ± 
<quantity box="[956,1039,221,244]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, ventral.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis box="[199,438,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">External morphology.</emphasis>
Body pale to uniformly brownish, lacking metameric patterns of pigmentation and also longitudinal lines on both ventral or dorsal surfaces (
<figureCitation box="[717,776,290,313]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. External morphology of Helobdella buzz. A. Entire leech, dorsal view showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow); B. Entire leech, ventral view; C. Ventral view of the anterior end; D. Dorsal view of the anterior end showing the eyespots (arrows); E. Ventral view of the genital region showing male (M) and female (F) gonopores; F. Lateral view of the anterior end showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801143/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–F); papillae and sensillae both absent; one pair of commashaped eyespots at 4/5, well separated from each other (
<figureCitation box="[746,805,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. External morphology of Helobdella buzz. A. Entire leech, dorsal view showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow); B. Entire leech, ventral view; C. Ventral view of the anterior end; D. Dorsal view of the anterior end showing the eyespots (arrows); E. Ventral view of the genital region showing male (M) and female (F) gonopores; F. Lateral view of the anterior end showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801143/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
D); nuchal scute absent; nuchal gland absent; protrusion of skin formed by muscular fibers from VII a1 to VIII a2 (
<figureCitation box="[739,802,360,383]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. External morphology of Helobdella buzz. A. Entire leech, dorsal view showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow); B. Entire leech, ventral view; C. Ventral view of the anterior end; D. Dorsal view of the anterior end showing the eyespots (arrows); E. Ventral view of the genital region showing male (M) and female (F) gonopores; F. Lateral view of the anterior end showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801143/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Figs 1</figureCitation>
F and 2A); male gonopore at XII a1/a2, female gonopore at XII a2/a3, separated by one primary annulus (
<figureCitation box="[646,707,394,417]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[255,1331,957,1867]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. External morphology of Helobdella buzz. A. Entire leech, dorsal view showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow); B. Entire leech, ventral view; C. Ventral view of the anterior end; D. Dorsal view of the anterior end showing the eyespots (arrows); E. Ventral view of the genital region showing male (M) and female (F) gonopores; F. Lateral view of the anterior end showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801143/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
E and 2C); two post-anal annuli; somites I-V: total of seven annuli; somite VI: ([a1+a2]+[a3]), sometimes ([a1]+[a2]+[a3]); somites VII-XXIV: triannulate, somite formula ([a1]+[a2]+[a3]); somite XXV: biannulate; somites XXVI and XXVII: uniannulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis box="[199,423,497,521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Internal morphology</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[440,506,498,521]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,244,1796,1818]" captionTargetBox="[401,1195,191,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[390,1196,191,1775]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Internal morphology of Helobdella buzz. A. atrium; ED. ejaculatory duct; G. ganglium; GC. gastric caecum; O. ovisac; P. proboscis; PC. post-caecum; SD. salivary duct; SG. salivary gland; T. testisac." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Base of pharynx in XIV; compact saliary glands in XIII (
<figureCitation box="[1166,1233,498,521]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1160,1182]" captionTargetBox="[250,1336,330,1139]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[250,1337,330,1139]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Longitudinal sections of Helobdella buzz. A. Nuchal region showing the internal structure of the protrusion of the skin; B. Segments XII-XIV showing the position of the compact salivary glands (arrow). C. Male (yellow arrow) and female (red arrow) gonopores. D. Genital region showing the compact salivary gland (arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801145/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
B and 2D); Linear salivary ducts in XII/XIII, at base of proboscis; six pairs of gastric caeca not inclined anteriorwards, last pair forming post-caeca; four pairs of intestinal caeca inclined anteriorwards; male atrium located anteriorly to ganglia XII; ejaculatory ducts with wide preatrial loop, ascendant part from XIII/XIV to XI/XII, forming loop of variable shape lateralwards in XII; six pairs of testisacs, first pair in XIII/XIV, last pair in XVIII/XIX; ovisacs tubular in XII, descending to XIV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="593" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Remarks.</emphasis>
The most remarkable external character of 
<taxonomicName box="[771,942,705,729]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[771,942,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Helobdella buzz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[948,1008,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[948,1008,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the protrusion of the skin from VII a1 to VIII a2. Two other species of leeches share the presence of similar protrusion, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ringuelet, 1948" authorityName="Ringuelet" authorityYear="1948" box="[1042,1354,740,764]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diploides">
<emphasis box="[1042,1174,740,764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">H. diploides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ringuelet" box="[1182,1354,741,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Ringuelet, R. (1948) Notas sobre Hirudineos Neotropicales V: Especies de la Republica del Paraguay. Notas del Museo de la Plata, 8, 213 - 244." type="journal article" year="1948">Ringuelet, 1948</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Siddall, 2001a" authorityName="Siddall" authorityYear="2001" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="nununununojensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">H. nununununojensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Siddall" box="[358,521,776,799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Siddall, M. E. (2001 a) Hirudinea from the Apolobamba in the Bolivian Andes, including three new species of Helobdella (Clitellata: Hirudinea). American Museum Novitates, 3341, 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="a">Siddall, 2001a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Among leeches belonging to 
<taxonomicName box="[876,1012,775,799]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diploides">
<emphasis box="[876,1012,775,799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">H. diploides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, the protrusion of the skin comprises a single primary annulus (VIII b1/b2) (
<bibRefCitation author="Iwama" box="[678,924,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Iwama, R. E. &amp; Arruda, E. P. (2016) Leeches of the genus Helobdella (Clitellata: Hirudinida) from Sao Paulo, Brazil with descriptions of two new species using micro-computed tomography and a new record of Barbronia weberi (Blanchard 1897). Zootaxa, 4144 (3), 411 - 429." type="journal article" year="2016">Iwama &amp; Arruda 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ringuelet" box="[934,1100,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Ringuelet, R. (1948) Notas sobre Hirudineos Neotropicales V: Especies de la Republica del Paraguay. Notas del Museo de la Plata, 8, 213 - 244." type="journal article" year="1948">Ringuelet 1948</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ringuelet" box="[1111,1169,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Ringuelet, R. (1985) Annulata: Hirudinea. Fundacion para la Educacion, la Ciencia y la Cultura, Buenos Aires, 321 pp." type="book" year="1985">1985</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, the internal morphology of 
<taxonomicName box="[320,452,844,868]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diploides">
<emphasis box="[320,452,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">H. diploides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite different, as the salivary glands are diffuse among members of that species, while among individuals belonging to 
<taxonomicName box="[496,576,879,903]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[496,576,879,903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">H. buzz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[582,642,880,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[582,642,880,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
there is one pair of compact salivary glands.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801143/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" targetBox="[255,1331,957,1867]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1890,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,1890,1912]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
External morphology of 
<taxonomicName box="[522,679,1891,1912]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz">
<emphasis box="[522,679,1891,1912]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Helobdella buzz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A. Entire leech, dorsal view showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow); B. Entire leech, ventral view; C. Ventral view of the anterior end; D. Dorsal view of the anterior end showing the eyespots (arrows); E. Ventral view of the genital region showing male (M) and female (F) gonopores; F. Lateral view of the anterior end showing the protrusion of the skin (arrow).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1435,152,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
Members of 
<taxonomicName authority="Siddall, 2001b" authorityName="Siddall" authorityYear="2001" box="[341,738,152,175]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="nununununojensis">
<emphasis box="[341,571,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H. nununununojensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Siddall" box="[580,738,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" refString="Siddall, M. E. (2001 b) Leeches of Laguna Volcan, Bolivia, including a new species of Helobdella (Clitellata: Hirudinea). American Museum Novitates, 3313, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="b">Siddall, 2001b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also possess a protrusion of the skin on the nuchal region and compact salivary glands, however, the protrusion of the skin is shorter in animals belonging to that species, restricted to VIII a1, and they have longer ejaculatory ducts, extending to XIX (
<bibRefCitation author="Siddall" box="[866,1018,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" refString="Siddall, M. E. (2001 a) Hirudinea from the Apolobamba in the Bolivian Andes, including three new species of Helobdella (Clitellata: Hirudinea). American Museum Novitates, 3341, 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="a">Siddall 2001a</bibRefCitation>
), while in leeches belonging to 
<taxonomicName box="[1356,1435,220,244]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1356,1435,220,244]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H. buzz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,211,256,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,211,256,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the ejaculatory ducts do not extend beyond XIII/XIV.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801145/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" targetBox="[250,1336,330,1139]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1160,1240]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1160,1182]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Longitudinal sections of 
<emphasis box="[511,672,1160,1181]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
<taxonomicName box="[511,669,1160,1181]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz">Helobdella buzz</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
A. Nuchal region showing the internal structure of the protrusion of the skin; B. Segments XII-XIV showing the position of the compact salivary glands (arrow). C. Male (yellow arrow) and female (red arrow) gonopores. D. Genital region showing the compact salivary gland (arrow).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1282,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
Members of two other species belonging to this genus share with specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1097,1180,1282,1306]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1097,1180,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H. buzz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1192,1256,1283,1306]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1192,1256,1283,1306]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the presence of compact salivary glands, 
<taxonomicName authority="Siddall 2001b" authorityName="Siddall" authorityYear="2001" box="[430,712,1314,1338]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sorojchi">
<emphasis box="[430,551,1314,1338]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H. sorojchi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Siddall" box="[561,712,1315,1338]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" refString="Siddall, M. E. (2001 b) Leeches of Laguna Volcan, Bolivia, including a new species of Helobdella (Clitellata: Hirudinea). American Museum Novitates, 3313, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="b">Siddall 2001b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[770,920,1314,1338]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bolivianita">
<emphasis box="[770,920,1314,1338]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H. bolivianita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
2001a, but members of the former species are easily differentiated from 
<taxonomicName box="[439,524,1346,1370]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[439,524,1346,1370]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H. buzz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[533,597,1347,1370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[533,597,1347,1370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having weak subdivisions of the primary annuli from VIII through XV (
<bibRefCitation author="Siddall" box="[158,312,1379,1402]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" refString="Siddall, M. E. (2001 b) Leeches of Laguna Volcan, Bolivia, including a new species of Helobdella (Clitellata: Hirudinea). American Museum Novitates, 3313, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="b">Siddall 2001b</bibRefCitation>
), while members of 
<taxonomicName box="[529,677,1378,1402]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bolivianita">
<emphasis box="[529,677,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H. bolivianita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have both diffuse and compact salivary glands, and also a nuchal scute at VIII (
<bibRefCitation author="Siddall" box="[236,389,1411,1434]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" refString="Siddall, M. E. (2001 a) Hirudinea from the Apolobamba in the Bolivian Andes, including three new species of Helobdella (Clitellata: Hirudinea). American Museum Novitates, 3341, 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="a">Siddall 2001a</bibRefCitation>
), which is absent in leeches belonging to 
<taxonomicName box="[832,911,1410,1434]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[832,911,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H. buzz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[918,978,1411,1434]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[918,978,1411,1434]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="593" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1282,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1443,1466]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after the Pixar’s character 
<taxonomicName box="[871,926,1443,1466]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="594" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz">Buzz</taxonomicName>
Lightyear, a toy space ranger hero of the Toy Story blockbuster. The epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[490,544,1475,1498]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz">buzz</taxonomicName>
” is used here in apposition according to the article 34.2.1 of the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (
<collectionCode box="[467,531,1507,1530]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">ICZN</collectionCode>
1999). The protrusion of the skin on the nuchal region of 
<taxonomicName box="[1155,1328,1506,1530]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1155,1328,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Helobdella buzz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1335,1393,1507,1530]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a main diagnostic characteristic and its size and location resemble an astronaut helmet, as that of 
<taxonomicName box="[1167,1222,1539,1562]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossiphoniidae" genus="Helobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchobdellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="594" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="buzz">Buzz</taxonomicName>
Lightyear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
